    <para id="import-auto-id1910951">The minus sign indicates that the negative charges are moving in the direction opposite to conventional current. The small value for drift velocity (on the order of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>4</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>m/s</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>) confirms that the signal moves on the order of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>12</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math> times faster (about <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>8</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>m/s</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>) than the charges that carry it.</para></example></section>

